South African Food Prices Add Pressure to Inflation, Daniel Mminele Says

-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 
2011-04-07T17:06:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/south-african-food-prices-add-pressure-to-inflation-daniel-mminele-says.html
Food prices in  South Africa  are
adding pressure to inflation while job creation remains a
“serious challenge” for the country, said  Daniel Mminele ,
deputy governor of the South African Reserve Bank.  There is “less room to manoeuvre” inside the country’s
inflation-target band, he said in a speech in  Pretoria  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Franz Wild in Johannesburg at 
 fwild@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
